		<td>
			<h1 align="center">User Strategies for Query Refinement</h1>
			<hr>			
			
			<h3>User Strategies for Query Refinement:</h3>
			When the system returns results back to the user, there are several 
			things user can do to refine their queries:<ol>
				<li>Parameter tuning - changing the parameters (favor color 
				feature or mixed feature).</li>
				<li>Bouncing - clicking in one of the retrieved images to launch 
				new query.</li>
				<li>Browsing - viewing the next page of results.</li>
			</ol>
			<p align="center">&nbsp;<i>Fig 1. Different refinement strategies 
			visualized in feature space</i><br>
			<img border="0" src="images/query-refinement.JPG" width="589" height="475"></td>
	</tr>
